# NurAI â€“ Visual Tokens (v1)
Version: 1.0

This document translates NurAI Visual DNA
into concrete but flexible visual tokens.

These tokens are NOT branding assets.
They are implementation-ready design constraints.

Exact values may evolve, relationships MUST NOT.

---

## ðŸŽ¨ COLOR TOKENS

Colors are intentionally low-saturation and warm.
They are designed to reduce cognitive load.

---

### ðŸŸ« COLOR: Background Base

Role:
- Main app background

Guidelines:
- Warm off-white
- Slight beige / parchment undertone
- Never pure white

Example direction (not mandatory):
- Light parchment
- Soft cream

Usage:
- App root background
- Reading screens

---

### ðŸŸ« COLOR: Surface / Card

Role:
- Cards and containers

Guidelines:
- 3â€“6% darker than Background Base
- Difference should be felt, not clearly seen

Usage:
- AyahCard
- ReadingCard
- Soft sections

---

### âš« COLOR: Primary Text

Role:
- Main readable text

Guidelines:
- Dark gray
- Never full black
- Comfortable for long reading

Usage:
- Ayah meanings
- Main paragraphs
- Core UI text

---

### âšª COLOR: Secondary Text

Role:
- Supporting text

Guidelines:
- Lighter gray
- Clearly secondary
- Must not compete with content

Usage:
- Labels
- Meta info
- Helper text

---

### ðŸŒ¿ COLOR: Accent (Very Limited)

Role:
- Subtle emphasis

Guidelines:
- Earthy tone (olive / clay / sand family)
- Desaturated
- Used sparingly

Rules:
- No large surfaces
- No backgrounds
- Never dominant

Usage:
- Active state indicators
- Soft highlights
- Gentle focus cues

---

## âœï¸ TYPOGRAPHY TOKENS

Typography carries NurAIâ€™s emotional weight.

---

### FONT ROLE 1: UI / Body Font

Purpose:
- Interface clarity
- Neutral communication

Characteristics:
- Sans-serif
- Humanist or neutral grotesk
- High readability
- No strong personality

Recommended candidates:
- Inter (acceptable but not branded)
- Source Sans 3
- IBM Plex Sans
- SF Pro (iOS native)

Rule:
If it draws attention to itself, itâ€™s wrong.

---

### FONT ROLE 2: Reading / Ayah Font

Purpose:
- Spiritual reading
- Calm reflection

Characteristics:
- Slight serif or humanist serif
- Soft contrast
- Modern, not traditional
- Book-like rhythm

Recommended candidates:
- Literata
- Source Serif 4
- Crimson Pro
- Charter

Rule:
Reading text should feel like a page, not a UI label.

---

## ðŸ“ SPACING TOKENS

Spacing is the primary visual identity.

Base unit:
- 8px system

Rules:
- Vertical spacing > horizontal spacing
- Cards must never feel tight
- One idea per section

Preferred gaps:
- Section spacing: 24â€“32px
- Card padding: 16â€“20px
- Line height: generous (1.4â€“1.6)

---

## ðŸ”˜ BUTTON TOKENS

Button philosophy:
- Low pressure
- Optional feeling

Preferred styles:
- Text buttons
- Soft outlined buttons
- Muted accent color only on interaction

Avoid:
- Solid bright buttons
- Aggressive primary CTAs
- Large block buttons everywhere

---

## ðŸŒ™ MOTION TOKENS

Motion is reassurance, not excitement.

Rules:
- Duration: slow (200â€“300ms)
- Easing: ease-out
- No bounce
- No attention-seeking animations

---

## ðŸš« VISUAL RESTRICTIONS

Do NOT use:
- Progress bars
- Streak visuals
- Achievement badges
- Loud gradients
- High-contrast color blocks

---

## ðŸ§­ FINAL IMPLEMENTATION RULE

When in doubt:
- Reduce contrast
- Increase spacing
- Remove decoration

Calm is the brand.

---

END OF VISUAL TOKENS
